1
00:00:02,841 --> 00:00:06,101
We should not think 
that our guru-varga

2
00:00:06,111 --> 00:00:14,813
that they’ve given so much for us 
to focus on in our study,

3
00:00:15,483 --> 00:00:20,131
and that they forgot,
some really important thing

4
00:00:20,131 --> 00:00:24,850
they forgot to tell us.
And we’ll find that!

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,330
[In The Spotlight]

6
00:00:29,130 --> 00:00:33,611
We see sometime 
in Goswāmī literature,
 

7
00:00:33,611 --> 00:00:40,241
when the Vraja-gopīs 
are pressed to respond

8
00:00:40,241 --> 00:00:47,252
in some particular situation
that they have extensive knowledge

9
00:00:47,252 --> 00:00:51,872
of the scriptures, Purāṇas … 
everything.

10
00:00:52,022 --> 00:01:00,703
And of Sanskrit language,
and all of its intricacies.

11
00:01:01,503 --> 00:01:06,712
So, they’re really …

12
00:01:06,712 --> 00:01:12,012
we’ll say that they 
are suppressing

13
00:01:12,012 --> 00:01:15,988
this sort of knowledge,
this aspect of themselves.

14
00:01:17,228 --> 00:01:22,964
It only comes out 
under service necessity.

15
00:01:25,073 --> 00:01:27,378
And as we see
in Gaura-līlā,

16
00:01:27,378 --> 00:01:34,563
it’s Braja-gopīs who take on
position of the Goswāmīs.

17
00:01:34,563 --> 00:01:37,587
And they are writing 
so many books …

18
00:01:37,587 --> 00:01:40,759
Jīva Goswāmī, the ultimate 
Sanskrit scholar;

19
00:01:40,759 --> 00:01:42,978
Rūpa, Sanātan, 
Raghunāth Dās—
 

20
00:01:42,978 --> 00:01:47,898
they are writing 
these incredible books;

21
00:01:47,898 --> 00:01:51,598
so many pastimes
in perfect Sanskrit.

22
00:01:52,065 --> 00:01:57,600
nānā-śāstra-vicāraṇaika-nipuṇau 
sad-dharma-saṁsthāpakau

23
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:01,770
lokānāṁ hita …
there you go again—lokānāṁ hita.

24
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:06,224
… kāriṇau tri-bhuvane mānyau śaraṇyākarau
[Ṣaḍ-goswāmī-aṣṭaka]

25
00:02:06,263 --> 00:02:10,764
They studied all these scriptures
and extracted from them

26
00:02:10,764 --> 00:02:13,745
for the benefit of everyone.

27
00:02:13,745 --> 00:02:20,535
So, really our focus should be
narrow in this sense.

28
00:02:20,535 --> 00:02:23,640
Like Guru Mahārāj said,
“Most exclusive …”

29
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:29,987
We’re narrowing our focus
to what is all-comprehensive.

30
00:02:31,304 --> 00:02:34,239
We need to focus 
on what’s been selected

31
00:02:34,239 --> 00:02:37,239
by the guru-varga 
as being substantial;

32
00:02:37,239 --> 00:02:43,959
become acquainted with that
and not avoiding that.

33
00:02:45,161 --> 00:02:46,949
What is the Bengali saying:

34
00:02:50,121 --> 00:02:51,251
The horse …

35
00:02:51,251 --> 00:02:54,162
What’s in front of the horse,
that’s called the trough.

36
00:02:54,162 --> 00:02:56,862
So, there is the trough 
full of food, and it says:

37
00:02:56,862 --> 00:03:03,283
“The horse jumps over the trough
and runs in search of food.”

38
00:03:04,612 --> 00:03:07,603
Bengalis are knowing
many things.

39
00:03:07,663 --> 00:03:09,943
[Laughing]

40
00:03:12,213 --> 00:03:16,812
So, they are serving nectar to us
on a golden plate.

41
00:03:16,823 --> 00:03:19,923
And we’re going:
“Is there going to be dessert?

42
00:03:19,923 --> 00:03:22,234
What is he eating 
over there?

43
00:03:22,234 --> 00:03:25,704
That guy over in the dark, 
I can’t see it.”

44
00:03:25,704 --> 00:03:28,234
[Laughing]

45
00:03:28,234 --> 00:03:30,514
We are own worst enemies.

46
00:03:30,514 --> 00:03:35,905
So, it’s better …
these things are so important,

47
00:03:35,905 --> 00:03:40,261
it’s better to err
on the side of caution.

